	  <p>
	  <input name="lang" id="generic" title="Choose generic conventions" onclick="return transtext_rmdv(0)" value="generic" type="radio" checked="checked"/>
	    Generic : Used with languages like Dravidian. No postprocessing.<br/>
	    <input name="lang" id="sanskrta" title="Choose Sanskrta conventions - which handles candrabindus differently and requires a Viráma at the end of words, unless they end witha schwa (a) " onclick="return transtext_rmdv(0)" value="sanskrta" type="radio" />
	     Old Indic : Sanskrta, Pali, Prakrits. Sandhi postprocessing <br/>
	    <input name="lang" class="style24" id="hindi" onclick="return transtext_rmdv(0)" title="Use New Indic conventions - like anunásiká nasal vowels, candrabindus and implied Viráma at end of words" value="hindi" type="radio" />
	    Modern North Indian : Hindi, Marathi, Nepali, Bangla ... . Scibal conventions. Inherits Old Indic.</p></td>
  
      <td><div align="center"><strong>Features and Ligatures </strong>
      </div>
        <p>Anusvára mode.:
          <input name="anu" class="style24" id="anu" title="Anusvára mode - turns half-nasals into anusváras as appropriate. Useful for new Indic Languages. Turn off for Sanskrta" onclick="return transtext_rmdv(0)" value="checkbox" type="checkbox" />
        </p></td>
   
